# Reports: every run writes a UNIQUE timestamped report (reports/report-<UTC>.html,
# enforced by tests/conftest.py pytest_configure) so no run can ever overwrite
# another. Those auto files are local-only / ignored; a report given a DESCRIPTIVE
# name (report-findings.html, report-full-live-<date>.html, report-suite-hermetic.html)
# is committed deliberately. See CLAUDE.md (report-archiving rule).
reports/report.html
reports/report-[0-9]*.html

# --- Private working notes (not for the public-facing repo) -------------------
# Mirrors the RAG repo: the planning notebook, the dense findings log, the
# article scribbles, and the next-project starter stay local. The public door is
# README + docs/walkthrough.md, which stand alone (PLAN.md discipline lesson 6).
PLAN.md
notes.md
article.md
plan-agent.md
working_with_ai.md
human-tasks.md
PORTFOLIO.md

# --- Tier-2 reliability side-experiment (private by decision) -----------------
# evidence/ and experiments/ ARE committed - the raw transcripts + finding
# writeups are useful and the published report carries the model output anyway
# (PLAN.md S6: ship unredacted, nothing actionable to redact). The sole
# exception is the tier-2 study: it is explicitly NOT red team and must appear
# in no public-facing file (PLAN.md: one theme; public files stand alone).
experiments/run_tier2.py
experiments/tier2-reliability.md
experiments/tier2-results.md
evidence/tier2-findings.md
evidence/tier2-raw-*.jsonl
evidence/tier2-run*.log
data/calibration/tier2_traps.yaml
